    "content_html_en": "<style>\n  body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.55;color:#111;margin:0;padding:0}\n  h1{font-size:14pt;text-align:center;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em;margin:0 0 2px}\n  .subtitle{text-align:center;font-size:10pt;color:#555;margin:0 0 2px}\n  h2{font-size:11pt;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.04em;margin:16px 0 6px;border-bottom:1px solid #999;padding-bottom:2px}\n  p{margin:6px 0}\n  .draft-banner{border:1px solid #b91c1c;color:#b91c1c;background:#fef2f2;font-size:9pt;font-weight:bold;text-align:center;padding:5px 8px;margin:0 0 12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.03em}\n  .fill{display:inline-block;min-width:140px;border-bottom:1px solid #333;line-height:1.1}\n  .sig-block{margin-top:14px}\n  table.schedule{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:9.5pt;margin:8px 0}\n  table.schedule th{background:#f0f0f0;padding:4px 6px;text-align:left;border:1px solid #ccc}\n  table.schedule td{padding:4px 6px;border:1px solid #ccc}\n</style>\n<div class=\"draft-banner\">DRAFT — for attorney review (Carl Barto). Not legal advice. Confirm all blanks and the employing entity before execution.</div>\n<h1>Lease-to-Own Asset Acquisition Agreement With Option to Purchase</h1>\n<p class=\"subtitle\">Version 1 — Carl Barto Original</p>\n<p>This Lease to Own Asset Acquisition Agreement with Option to Purchase (this “Agreement”) is made and entered into as of {{effective_date}}, 2026, by and between IH 35 Trucking, LLC, a Texas limited liability company (“Seller”), and {{buyer_name}} (“Buyer”) (each a “Party,” and collectively the “Parties”).</p>\n<h2>RECITALS</h2>\n<p>The Parties intend for Buyer to operate certain commercial motor vehicles (the “Trucks”) under its own insurance and permits, at its own expense; to reimburse Seller for the use of the Trucks; and to establish the obligation to purchase the Trucks at the conclusion of the lease. Upon payment of all amounts required herein, Seller shall transfer title to the Trucks to Buyer. This is strictly a lease-purchase acquisition with an option to purchase; neither Party shall acquire any interest in the other by reason of this Agreement.</p>\n<h2>NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants herein, the Parties agree as follows:</h2>\n<h2>1.  Identification of Trucks; Lease-to-Purchase Terms</h2>\n<p>The Trucks subject to this Agreement, together with each Truck’s make, model and year; Vehicle Identification Number; current lienholder (if any); balance owed to the lienholder; monthly lease payment (exclusive of the use charge); and monthly payment due date, are identified on the term sheet attached as Exhibit A and incorporated herein by reference.</p>\n<h2>2.  Use Charge</h2>\n<p>In addition to the monthly payment set forth in Exhibit A, Buyer shall pay to Seller, monthly, a fee equal to {{use_charge_percent}} percent ({{use_charge_percent}}%) of the amounts invoiced to third parties for loads hauled by each Truck.</p>\n<h2>3.  Option to Purchase</h2>\n<p>At the conclusion of the Lease Term, Buyer may purchase any Truck by paying to Seller the then fair market value of such Truck. Upon receipt of such amount, Seller shall transfer a clean certificate of title, free of liens, to Buyer.</p>\n<h2>4.  Lease Term</h2>\n<p>The lease term shall be {{lease_term_months}} months from the date of execution by both Parties (the “Term”). Buyer shall make the monthly lease payment for each Truck stated in Exhibit A throughout the Term.</p>\n<h2>5.  Inspection and Acceptance</h2>\n<p>Buyer may inspect all assets, maintenance records, ECM data, title records, payoff balances, and lender documentation prior to acceptance. Each Truck shall be individually accepted by a written Asset Acceptance Certificate, and may be purchased individually upon conclusion of its respective Term and payment of all consideration required herein.</p>\n<h2>6.  Representations</h2>\n<p>Each Party represents that it has the legal right and authority to enter into this Agreement. All liens on the Trucks have been disclosed in Exhibit A.</p>\n<h2>7.  Insurance</h2>\n<p>Buyer shall maintain, from the execution date, liability and physical-damage insurance in amounts sufficient to protect Seller, naming Seller as an additional insured with coverage of not less than $1,000,000 per occurrence, and as loss payee for replacement value. Failure to maintain insurance is an immediate event of default, whereupon Buyer shall immediately surrender the Trucks to Seller.</p>\n<h2>8.  Maintenance; Inspection; GPS Access</h2>\n<p>Maintenance of the Trucks shall be Buyer’s obligation upon execution. Seller may inspect the Trucks upon one (1) day’s written notice and shall retain access to maintenance logs and to the GPS location of the Trucks until Buyer fulfills all obligations hereunder. Upon a maintenance default, Seller may provide ten (10) days’ written notice to cure; if uncured, Seller may cancel Buyer’s right to possess or use the affected Truck, which Buyer shall immediately surrender.</p>\n<h2>9.  Assignability; Covenant Against Encumbering</h2>\n<p>This Agreement binds the Parties’ successors and assigns. Neither Party may sell, refinance, transfer, pledge, collateralize, or otherwise further encumber the Trucks subject to this Agreement.</p>\n<h2>10.  Remedies; Indemnification</h2>\n<p>Except for failures to maintain or insure the Trucks, a breach entitles the non-defaulting Party to damages, specific performance, equitable relief, and attorneys’ fees where allowed by applicable law. Buyer shall indemnify and hold Seller harmless from any and all claims arising from operation of the Trucks while subject to this Agreement.</p>\n<h2>11.  Governing Law; Venue</h2>\n<p>This Agreement is governed by the laws of the State of Texas, and the exclusive venue for any action to enforce it is Webb County, Texas.</p>\n<h2>IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have executed this Agreement as of the date first written above.</h2>\n<p>SELLER:  IH 35 Trucking, LLC</p>\n<p>By: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Name:  Jorge Muñoz</p>\n<p>Title:  Manager</p>\n<p>Date: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>BUYER:  <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>By: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Name: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Title: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Date: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h2>NOTARY ACKNOWLEDGMENTS</h2>\n<p>STATE OF TEXAS  §  COUNTY OF WEBB  §</p>\n<p>This instrument was acknowledged before me on the <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span> day of <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span>, 2026, by Jorge Muñoz, Manager of IH 35 Trucking, LLC, on behalf of said company.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span>   Notary Public, State of Texas</p>\n<p>This instrument was acknowledged before me on the <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span> day of <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span>, 2026, by <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span>, on behalf of Buyer.</p>\n<p><span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span>   Notary Public, State of Texas</p>\n<h2>EXHIBIT A — TERM SHEET (VEHICLE SCHEDULE)</h2>\n<p>Unit No.</p>\n<p>Year</p>\n<p>Make / Model</p>\n<h2>VIN</h2>\n<p>Lienholder</p>\n<p>Balance / Monthly</p>\n<p>Due Date</p>\n<p>1</p>\n<p>2</p>\n<p>3</p>\n<p>4</p>\n<p>5</p>\n<p>6</p>\n<p>7</p>\n<p>8</p>\n<p>9</p>\n<p>10</p>\n<p>For each Truck: make, model, year; VIN; lienholder (if any); balance owed; monthly lease payment (exclusive of the use charge); and monthly payment due date.</p>",
