    "content_html_en": "<style>\n  body{font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:11pt;line-height:1.55;color:#111;margin:0;padding:0}\n  h1{font-size:14pt;text-align:center;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em;margin:0 0 2px}\n  .subtitle{text-align:center;font-size:10pt;color:#555;margin:0 0 2px}\n  h2{font-size:11pt;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.04em;margin:16px 0 6px;border-bottom:1px solid #999;padding-bottom:2px}\n  p{margin:6px 0}\n  .draft-banner{border:1px solid #b91c1c;color:#b91c1c;background:#fef2f2;font-size:9pt;font-weight:bold;text-align:center;padding:5px 8px;margin:0 0 12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.03em}\n  .fill{display:inline-block;min-width:140px;border-bottom:1px solid #333;line-height:1.1}\n  .sig-block{margin-top:14px}\n  table.schedule{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:9.5pt;margin:8px 0}\n  table.schedule th{background:#f0f0f0;padding:4px 6px;text-align:left;border:1px solid #ccc}\n  table.schedule td{padding:4px 6px;border:1px solid #ccc}\n</style>\n<div class=\"draft-banner\">DRAFT — for attorney review (Carl Barto). Not legal advice. Confirm all blanks and the employing entity before execution.</div>\n<h1>Employee Non-Disclosure Agreement</h1>\n<p class=\"subtitle\">Confidentiality only — drivers / low-access roles</p>\n<p>This Agreement (the “Agreement”) is entered into by IH 35 {{company_entity_suffix}} (“Company”) and {{employee_name}} (“Employee”). In consideration of the commencement or continuation of Employee’s employment with Company and the compensation paid, Employee and Company agree as follows:</p>\n<h2>1.  Company’s Confidential Information</h2>\n<p>In the performance of Employee’s job duties with Company, Employee will be exposed to Company’s Confidential Information. “Confidential Information” means information or material that is commercially valuable to Company and not generally known or readily ascertainable in the industry, including, but not limited to: customer, shipper, consignee, broker, carrier, vendor, and driver lists and contact information; rates, pricing, fuel advances, settlements, margins, lane and load history, bids, and broker/customer preferences; dispatch, routing, border-crossing, drayage, compliance, and safety procedures; claims, factoring, insurance, and financing information; driver and employee files, compensation, qualifications, CDL/medical status, safety and accident history, and recruiting sources; TMS/ERP, QuickBooks/QBO, Samsara/ELD/telematics, and bank data, passwords, credentials, reports, templates, and business documents; and any other information not generally known to the public which, if misused or disclosed, could reasonably be expected to adversely affect Company’s business.</p>\n<h2>2.  Nondisclosure of Confidential Information</h2>\n<p>Employee shall keep Company’s Confidential Information, whether or not prepared or developed by Employee, in the strictest confidence, shall not disclose it to anyone outside Company without Company’s prior written consent, and shall not use it for Employee’s own purposes or the benefit of anyone other than Company. Employee shall not transfer Company information to personal email, personal cloud storage, personal phone accounts, messaging apps, USB drives, or third-party systems unless expressly authorized in writing by Company. Employee shall have no obligation to treat as confidential any information that (a) was lawfully in Employee’s possession without confidentiality obligation before disclosure by Company; (b) is or becomes public knowledge through no fault of Employee; or (c) is or becomes lawfully available to Employee from a source other than Company.</p>\n<h2>3.  Confidential Information of Others</h2>\n<p>Employee will not disclose to Company, use in Company’s business, or cause Company to use, any trade secret or confidential information of others.</p>\n<h2>4.  Return of Materials</h2>\n<p>When Employee’s employment with Company ends, for whatever reason, Employee will promptly deliver to Company all originals and copies of all documents, records, software, media, devices, fuel cards, toll tags, ELD devices, load documents, and other materials containing or constituting Company property or Confidential Information, and will permanently delete Company information from personal devices and accounts, certifying deletion in writing if requested.</p>\n<h2>5.  Confidentiality Obligation Survives Employment</h2>\n<p>Employee’s obligation to maintain the confidentiality and security of Confidential Information remains after Employee’s employment ends — for trade secrets, for so long as the information remains a trade secret, and for other Confidential Information, for three (3) years after separation unless a longer period is permitted by law or the information remains non-public and commercially sensitive.</p>\n<h2>6.  General Provisions</h2>\n<p>(a) Relationships. Nothing in this Agreement makes Employee a partner or joint venturer of Company. (b) Severability. If a court finds any provision invalid or unenforceable, the remainder shall be interpreted to best effect the intent of the Parties. (c) Integration. This Agreement is the complete understanding of the Parties on its subject matter and supersedes all prior agreements; it may be amended only in a writing signed by both Parties. (d) Waiver. Failure to exercise any right is not a waiver of prior or subsequent rights. (e) Injunctive Relief. Misappropriation of Confidential Information may cause Company irreparable harm difficult to quantify; Company may seek injunctive relief and any other relief available, in addition to its other remedies. (f) Indemnity. Employee agrees to indemnify Company against losses, damages, claims, or expenses resulting from Employee’s breach. (g) Attorney Fees. In any dispute arising out of this Agreement, the prevailing party may recover its reasonable attorneys’ fees and costs. (h) Governing Law. This Agreement is governed by the laws of the State of Texas. (i) Venue. Exclusive venue for any action arising out of or relating to this Agreement is the state and federal courts serving Webb County, Texas, and Employee consents to such jurisdiction and venue. (j) Successors &amp; Assigns. This Agreement binds each party’s heirs, successors, and assigns. Company may assign this Agreement at any time; Employee may not assign without Company’s prior written consent, and any assignment in violation is void.</p>\n<h2>7.  Protected Rights; Defend Trade Secrets Act Notice</h2>\n<p>Nothing in this Agreement prohibits Employee from reporting possible violations of law to a government agency, cooperating with a government investigation, filing a charge, or testifying truthfully, or (for employees covered by the National Labor Relations Act) from discussing wages, hours, or working conditions. Under 18 U.S.C. § 1833(b), an individual is not liable under any federal or state trade-secret law for disclosing a trade secret in confidence to a government official or attorney solely to report or investigate a suspected violation of law, or in a court filing made under seal.</p>\n<p>Employee has carefully read all of this Agreement and agrees that the restrictions set forth are fair and reasonably required to protect Company’s interests. Employee has received a copy of this Agreement as signed by the Parties.</p>\n<h2>COMPANY</h2>\n<p>Printed Name: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Title: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Signature: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Date: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<h2>WORKER</h2>\n<p>Printed Name: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Title: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Signature: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>Date: <span class=\"fill\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
